review_blob: Little, to no, aroma. Color certainly qualifies as porter. Light coffee taste, with a full toasted/charred finish. It seems more bitter than toasted.
Light pumpkin aroma. Pours a clear, pumpkin amber color with a thin head. Pumpkin taste very present, with the warmness of alcohol.

Great beer! Full aroma of vanilla and caramel. Poured super foamy, so, I had to wait a few moments before drinking. Flavor full of vanilla and caramel. It also has a hint of smoke. Textbook coloring for stout. Despite the increased BAC, it is well hidden in the flavor.
beer_name: Southern Tier Blackwater Series: Creme Brulee Stout

review_blob: Aroma of orange peel, and varied citrus notes. Pours a copper/amber color with a full, frothy white head. The taste starts with a well balanced front and middle. The finish is medium/full bitter.
Poor color, poor aroma, poor taste, poor palate. Shitty beer, top to bottom. Did I say that it is shitty?

Aroma of floral, chocolate, caramel and spice. An appearence of brown.black, classic porter color. A sweet taste on the front end, fillled with spice, a medium bodied middle and a subtle bitter finish.
Pours a light copper, with a medium sized, white head. Nice aroma full of pine and resin. The hoppy flavor is filled with grapefruit and finishes a medium bitter bite.
The color is cloudy orangish-yellow. Pours a thin white head Excellent raroma with notes of resin, spruce and citrus. Smooth, ballanced front end and finishes with a medium bitter note.
Pours a cloudy, dark golden. Appears thick and syrup-like (much like honey). The flavor has a syrup-like quality. The alcohol is very forward. Has a slight bitter finish.
Pours a golden copper. Light notes of grapefruit in the aroma. The taste has a super bitter finish, and a strange metallic aftertaste. Quite possibly the worst IPA ever.
Excellent red ale. Pours a clear amber with an off-white head. Aroma of pine and resin. The taste starts with a smooth well balanced malty taste, and finishes with a medium bitter quality.

Aroma of coffee and chocolate. Excellent malty taste, with coffee and chocolate highlights. Pours a deep ebony with a tan, chocolaty head. Sweet flavor with a nice balanced bitter finished. This may be my favorite porter of all time.
Aroma of pine. Pours a clear copper. Fresh piney hops on the front end of the taste with a nice bitter finish.
Super clear, bright golden color, filled with carbonation/bubbles. Nice aroma for a blonde with hints of honey and citrus. Demure hop quality that finishes smooth and well balanced
Nice, full bodied aroma. pours a cloudy amber with a medium white head. A taste with a sweet malty front end, and a medium bitter finish. Another winner from SoPro.

Green bottle = skunky aroma. Super carbonated and a clear yellow/golden piss color. Sweet taste on the front end and a clean, unchallenged finished. Very similar to a Heineken, another green bottle skunky beer.
Excellent aroma, full body, well balanced. Tan head. Smooth finish. Grainy aroma
Pours a deep black with a dark head. Roasty aroma with smoky notes. Flavor is smokey with a bitter finish. I was expecting more heat in flavor, but the smoke is very up front.

An aroma of tropical and citrus fruits. I dont feel the hoppy quality of an IPA in the taste. The palate is thick and heavy. Boozy as hell. Tasty, but an IPA? Maybe the high ABV is overwhelming the hop quality.
Not much of an aroma. Pours a deep black with a tan head, minimal lacing. Nice, full bodied flavor, hints of bourbon and a super malty sweetness.
Excellent beer! Pours a full copper color with a full body hop aroma filled with grapefruit and citrus. The taste is lightly malty with a moderately bitter finish.
Pours a hazy, golden amber. Aroma off citrus and pine. A citrus hop character, with a piney hops sprinkled in. The flavor is a bit bready with a moderate bitter finish.
Floral aroma. Pours a copperish-red color. Easy drinking, non-deScript front end, and middle. The finish is a moderate bitter.
Orangish, golden in color. Super foamy. Sour flavor with light hop character.
Fruity aroma and pours golden, with a hint of cloudiness. Super carbonated, with a fluffy white head. The flavor has a hint of bananas and creaminess, much like a cream ale.
Aroma of grape juice. Pours a cloudy/unfiltered brown. The taste is of grapes, light on the hop character with a dry finish.
Orange/copper in color, a bit on the cloudy side. Citrus in aroma and well represented in taste. The slightest hop quality on the back end.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Ovila Saison - Mandarin Orange & Peppercorns

review_blob: Sweet aroma with a taste that follows suit. Not a bad flavor for a blonde, well balanced taste. The color is a negative for me.
Palate was that of full body, creamy, average carbonation. Nice taste hints of cinnamon, and spice with a full bitter finish. The aroma could have been more pronounced.
Not much on aroma. The color doesnt Ill me howev, the taste is great. Nice, full bodied barleywine with a nice bitter finish.
Fruity aroma, chestnut brown color. Bold fruity flavor with a warm alcohol mouthfeel. Raisin and currant flavor strong. Not so sure about the clove presence.
UPDATED: MAR 21, 2015
Great copper color and a wonderful peach aroma. Malty flavor with a slight bitter finish.
Great color. Rich chocolaty head. Bursting with fruity alcohol aroma. Damn, what a kick of alcohol in the taste.
Sweet aroma with coffee hints. Nice full body flavor with light toasty notes and hints of chocolate.
No aroma. Pours a dark chocolate. Tastes of chocolate and roasted coffee. Light bitter finish.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Rain Check Spiced Stout

review_blob: Medium tan head, and poured a deep ebony. Fruity aroma. Sweet and malty on the front end of the taste, and finished with a light bitterness.

Pours a hazy golden color with a light white head. Lacing is abundant. Aroma is hoppy with hints of floral and herbs. Taste is well balanced on the front and and middle. It has a moderate bitter finish.
Pours a deep black with an aroma of light bourbon and oak. The ABV comes through in the flavor and the bourbon barrel is very forward in the taste. Super malty with a full bitter finish.
beer_name: Abita Bourbon Street Barrel Aged Imperial Stout

review_blob: Pours a thick, deep ebony with a nice tan head. Aroma is minimal. Super smooth, malty taste with a medium bitter finish. Nice offering from SPB
Roasted chocolaty, citrus and pine aroma that pours a deep black, with a tan head. The flavor is full bodied with a distinct bitter/hoppy finish.
Pours a beautiful bright golden with a shiny white head. Aroma of pine and citrus. Well balanced taste with a slight bitter finish.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Snow Wit White IPA

review_blob: UPDATED: JAN 10, 2015
Pours a golden amber. Fluffy off-white head. Average aroma, at best. Sweet malt on the front end with a full bitter finish.
Pours a medium color of amber and a thin non existent head. Little to no aroma, with a taste to match.
Wonderful aroma of citrus, resin and pine. Great taste of malt with a hyper-hoppy flavor with a full finish.
Malty aroma, pours a deep ebony with a thin brown head. Malty taste with hints of alcohol.
Pours an orangish-amber with a thin white head. An aroma with barely noticeable spices and a taste to match.
Pours a deep caramel/mahogany with a thin, off white head. Beautiful color on this one. An aroma of hay, grass malt. Very light hop flavor with a smooth finish, maybe a hint of bitterness on the end.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Victory Beer Camp Alt Route

review_blob: Pours a deep copper, with the aroma of grass and grain. The flavor has a horse blanket, leather quality and a slightly sour finish.
